I am a 28 YO female, married for 2 and a half years. I have always had irregular periods since my puberty and now I was planning to conceive  hence, the visit to this doctor. She recommended some  tests and scans to check my fertility and the underlying problem for my irregular periods. Now, after the tests it turns out that my AMH level was dangerously low which indicates low fertility and requires treatment like IVF for conceiving. But to my utter shock the doctor paid no heed to it and did not even bother to explain my medical condition.

Ironically, for the next 6 months, she had actually put me on various contraceptive pills and some ayurvedic tonic to regularize my periods ****** *** ***** ********* ********* ** ********** ******* *** **** *** ** ********** ** ********* ********* ***** **** ***** ******** *** ***** ********* ********* *** I was not comfortable changing the doctor while I was already under medication (contraceptive pills as prescribed by her) for regularizing my periods. 

Finally, when the prescribed course of contraceptives was over I switched to another doctor (she's a renowned doctor from a reputed hospital of Hyderabad) and in the first trans vaginal scan itself  they detected an abnormality in the shape of my uterus, which is from my birth. ** ** ***** ******** *** ***** ****** ***** *** ****** *** ****  **** ***** ** * ************* ****** FYI, each trans-vaginal scan in cradle costs Rs. 1500/- and this hospital where I am currently going charges only Rs.450/- . Huge difference in the price *** *** *** **********
